<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-03T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-03T02:00:00-05:00" n="370" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12777: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-03T15:00:00+08:00">August 3, 1934—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 3—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>337. Reference the Legation’s telegram No. 334 of August 2, 5 p.m.,
                            Commander in Chief of the United States Asiatic Fleet informs me that he
                            has ordered U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Sacramento</hi> to proceed
                            immediately to Pagoda Anchorage. Foochow informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>